## purpose
Defines the canonical architectural role of housing in CivilizationOS.

## design_intent
Housing is the bounded living-place structure
through which residence,
occupancy,
access,
placement,
and domestic continuity
become meaningful.

Housing is not merely a map point or asset label.
It is the governed habitation boundary
for actors and their belongings.

## architectural_position
Housing sits between:
- world and nation location meaning
- life continuity
- family co-residence
- item/inventory placement
- access and privacy boundary
- housing-related operations and policy

## required_behavior
- housing identity must remain explicit
- occupancy basis must remain explicit
- access scope must remain explicit
- current and historical housing states must remain distinguishable
- placement boundary must remain explicit

## canonical_rules
- location presence does not imply housing authority
- occupancy does not imply unrestricted access
- historical residence must remain distinguishable from current residence
- item placement must not redefine housing truth
- ambiguous occupancy or access fails closed

## state_model
The housing domain distinguishes:
- proposed housing
- active housing
- restricted housing
- partially occupied housing
- historical housing
- closed housing

## actor_boundary
- housing owner
- resident
- guest
- operator
- reviewer
- adapter

## decision_matrix
- if housing identity is unclear, stop access-sensitive paths
- if occupancy basis is unclear, fail closed
- if access scope exceeds role, deny
- if housing becomes historical, preserve residence trace
- if housing closes, preserve historical occupancy and placement trace

## review_checklist
- housing identity is explicit
- occupancy model is explicit
- access boundary is explicit
- historical distinction is explicit
